On Thu, Mar 26, 2009 at 1:54 PM, Anmol Bhasin &lt;anmol.bhasin@...&gt;wrote:

&gt;   Hi,
&gt;
&gt; Heritrix canonicalization routines are not meant to create URLs for
&gt; fetching. The main purpose is to use it to filter out URLs that have been
&gt; previously seen and need not be scheduled again. For this purpose you need
&gt; to bring down the URL to its barebones form which includes lowercasing so
&gt; that the Hash signatures of the canonicalized URLs are insensitive to case
&gt; differences.
&gt;
&gt; So in short, Canonicalized URLs are not meant for fetching but only for
&gt; Hash Signature generation for filtering previously seen URLs.
&gt;
&gt; Hope this helps.
&gt;
&gt; Anmol
